<section class="card">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>Are frost dates guaranteed?</summary>
    <p>
      No. They represent historical averages at the 32°F (0°C) threshold.
      Individual years can vary.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Should I plant exactly on my last frost date?</summary>
    <p>
      Usually not. Many gardeners wait until nighttime temperatures
      remain consistently above 50°F (10°C) for warm-season crops.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Does this apply in Canada as well?</summary>
    <p>
      Yes. The frost-based method works anywhere seasonal freezing occurs.
      The dataset includes both U.S. ZIP codes and Canadian postal FSAs.
    </p>
  </details>
</section>

